🔒 Thread Safety Guarantees

LoamSpine ensures:
   ✅ No data races
   ✅ Sequential consistency
   ✅ Chain integrity maintained
   ✅ No lost updates

How it works:
   • Spine wrapped in Arc<Mutex<T>>
   • Mutex ensures exclusive write access
   • Each append is atomic
   • Chain links always valid

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
💡 Concurrency Best Practices

DO ✅:
   • Use Arc<Mutex<Spine>> for shared access
   • Keep critical sections small
   • Release locks between operations
   • Handle errors gracefully
   • Consider batching for high throughput

DON'T ❌:
   • Don't hold locks across async boundaries
   • Don't share Spine without synchronization
   • Don't ignore append errors
   • Don't create excessive contention

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
🎯 Concurrent Use Cases

Multi-User Systems:
   • Multiple users appending to shared spine
   • Example: Collaborative audit log

High-Throughput Ingestion:
   • Multiple data sources → single spine
   • Example: IoT sensor aggregation

Distributed Workers:
   • Worker pool processing tasks
   • Example: Job result logging

Real-Time Analytics:
   • Concurrent writes + reads
   • Example: Live event tracking

